<L>__{interior funeral home. eliot's room same time}
<A>__{eliot carefully pins anna's polaroid to the wall.}
<B>__{on polaroids}
<A>__{we pan slowly across the other photographs we saw before. but now we look at them differently. in some faces there is the glimmer of life. in some a despairing pleading look. in others passive resignation. eliot's room eliot moves towards the window. eliot's pov the dark cemetery. in the distance flickering candles illuminate anna's grave.}
<C>__{eliot }
<D>__{imagine anna. the whole world, your mother, your fiancee, your friends. everyone has buried you. they've placed a stone above your body.}
<A>__{eliot's room}
<C>__{eliot}
<D>__{they've said their good byes and gone back to their tv dinners and shopping malls. thinking that this is never going to happen to them. until it's their turn to be buried. think about it anna...}
<A>__{eliot glances at his watch.}
<C>__{eliot}
<D>__{...think about it while you still can.}
